 adult entertainment environment and it cannot be denied that the gaming industry has created tens of thousands of jobs and streamed countless millions of tax revenues into the state still when you first arrive in town the contrast between the hulking casinos and the squalor that surrounds them is a shock frankly the place can look like a collaboration of bukowski and bosch then as you start to get a sense of how the streets operate and who the players are the not so hidden economy of sin seeking tourists drug dealers hustlers and street walkers there's the thrill of gaining secret specialized knowledge atlantic city is truly one of most fascinating places i have ever been and for the journalist and the junkie alike the action of street life is an addiction all its own but after a while as you become attached to people whose lives are so sad and hopeless reporting becomes an emotional ordeal it is hard to wade through all the human wreckage of the city's dark side without absorbing some of the suffering one witnesses after three days there you want desperately to leave of course once you've left you can think only about going back escapenumber it may be easy for people to dismiss the murders as a story of four women who succumbed to their own bad judgment and worse luck others may see the killer as a something of an allegorical figure a human embodiment of the danger and damage of drug addiction but if there's one thing i hope the viewers remember it is that these women for all their problems were very real human beings they all had families and friends who loved them they all had young children and whatever bad choices they'd made none of them deserved this escapenumber miguel sancho escapenumber escapenumber hours mystery airs saturday at escapenumberpmet escapenumberct escapenumber if you would like more information on any of these stories or the broadcast please click on the following address and e mail us at escapenumber escapenumberhours cbsnews com escapenumb